hopobject.body: An estate agents peppharmsale.com "What [Fed Chairman Ben] Bernanke's been trying to do for the past few weeks is push the marketplace into the notion that tapering and the end of quantitative easing is going to be later rather than sooner," said Jim Wyckoff, senior analyst at Kitco. "And I think he's done a good job of convincing the marketplace of that. That's what pressured the dollar, and it's been a bit bullish for raw commodities."
